---
1. Maglev â€œFanâ€ in Vacuum
Without air to push against, a conventional fan or turbine has nothing to act on.
If you replace the rotor with magnetic fields accelerating charged particles, you are expelling mass electrically.
---
2. That is the Definition of an Ion Engine
Ion engines work by accelerating ions (charged atoms) with electric fields.
They produce thrust in a vacuum by ejecting these ions at very high velocity.
Your maglev â€œrotorlessâ€ setup is essentially a high-RPM-equivalent ion accelerator.
Differences vs. conventional ion engines:
Traditional ion engines accelerate ions linearly through grids or electrostatic/magnetic fields.
Your concept could:
Use maglev-style magnetic acceleration, potentially faster and more efficient.
Be scaled up to megawatt-class for serious thrust instead of tiny spacecraft maneuvers.
---
3. Implications
In atmosphere: you still need air or some propellant to push against to get â€œjet-likeâ€ thrust.
In vacuum: yes, itâ€™s functionally an ion engine, just with potentially higher power density and extreme â€œRPM-equivalentâ€ acceleration.
You could call it a maglev ion thrusterâ€”a rotorless, high-speed plasma accelerator.
---
